    "description": "Tsudakoma Corp. produces and sells textile machinery and machine tool attachments in Japan, Asia, North and south America, Europe, and internationally. It operates through two segments, Textile Machinery Business and Machine Tool Related Business. The company offers textile machinery comprising air jet looms, water jet looms, and preparatory machines. It also provides composite machinery, such as prepreg slitters, automated fiber lay-up machines, auto lay-up machines, multi-axial UD auto lay-up systems, auto edge welding machines, profile molding machines, carbon fiber rapier looms, and drape forming systems. In addition, the company offers machines, including NC rotatory tables, machine vises, and manual tables. Further, it provides castings for textile machinery and preparation machinery, machine tool attachments, and various industrial machinery. The company was formerly known as TSUDAKOMA Industrial Co., Ltd. and changed its name to Tsudakoma Corp. in 1982. Tsudakoma Corp. was founded in 1909 and is headquartered in Kanazawa, Japan."
